                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Gale, who keeps the George public-house in George-court, Adelphi. The prisoner came on the 4th of July, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, for a pint of beer—he offered me a half-crown—I saw that it was bad—I told him so—he said was it—I kept it—I bit it, and gave it the officer.</p>
